<h1>LED Tutorial</h1>

<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Raspberry Pi connected to the internet</li>
  <li>LED, breadboard, wires, 330 Ohm resistor</li>
</ul>

<br><br>

<h4>1. Set up the circuit</h4>
Connect the LED to GPIO pin #4, and add a 330 Ohm resistor (see circuit diagram).
<br>
<%= image_tag('tutorials/led_off.jpg') %>

<br><br>

<h4>2. Install LimitOS on the Raspberry Pi</h4>
<%= render 'shared/install_command' %>
<br>
<%= image_tag('tutorials/limitos_install.gif') %>

<br><br>

<h4>3. Add pin #4 as a digital output</h4>
You can then click the "on" or "off" buttons on the LimitOS website to turn the LED on or off.
<br>
<%= image_tag('tutorials/led_on.jpg') %>
